short_title: Microsoft: Trickbot Network Could Disrupt Election
short_description: Microsoft took action against Trickbot, a botnet (network of devices infected with malware). Microsoft warned that Trickbot could spread ransomware, which might be used to disrupt the presidential election.

short_title: Facebook: Inauthentic Accounts Based in Romania
short_description: Facebook removed 35 accounts, 3 pages, and 88 Instagram accounts originating in Romania. The accounts posed as Americans, amplified each other’s content, and managed pages posing as President Trump fan pages. In addition to reposting stories by American conservative news outlets, the network discussed the 2020 election, support for the Trump campaign by African Americans, conservative ideology, Christian beliefs, and QAnon.

short_title: Reuters: Louisiana Hacks Possibly Tied to North Korea
short_description: The Louisiana National Guard was called in to stop a series of ransomware attacks that have hit small government offices in recent weeks. Experts were unable to attribute the attack to any specific actor, although they did note that the hackers used a tool associated with the North Korean government. It is unclear whether the hackers were targeting election-related systems or simply trying to extort money, and the cyberattack was stopped before significant harm was done.

disinformant_attribution: Non-Aligned Commercial Enterprise (attribution to apolitical commercial actor)
short_title: Zenger News: Biden, Harris Followers are Indian Sockpuppets
short_description: Zenger News, an online wire service, claimed that the Twitter accounts of Joe Biden and Kamala Harris have thousands of fake followers purchased from troll farms in rural India.
